Cross browser date picker component

react-datepicker
npm install --save react-datepicker

import DatePicker from 'react-datepicker'
import 'react-datepicker/dist/react-datepicker.css'

DatePicker takes in 2 props
1. selected - represents the date selected
2. onChange evt handler

<DatePicker selected={} onChange={} />


Different props that can be used on DatePicker component
1. dateFormat
    NOTE: make sure that 'MM' is in uppercase
    dateFormat="yyyy/MM/dd"

2. minDate & maxDate props
minDate={}
maxDate={}

3. To filter dates
Also this is how to check for weekends in JS
filterDate={date => date.getDay() !== 6 && date.getDay() !== 0}

4. isClearable
if this is specified or set to true, we will get a 'clear' button when a date is selected.

5. For a year dropdown
showYearDropdown
scrollableMonthYearDropdown
